Portugal, a signatory of the UN Kyoto Protocol, aims to generate 39% of its electricity from renewables like solar and wind power.
Plans are underway for the world's largest solar energy station in the Alentejo region, set to create 240 jobs.
Meanwhile, a Dutch team won a solar car race in Australia, showcasing the potential of solar energy.
In the Philippines, a solar project funded by Spain will bring electricity to rural areas.
Taiwan is also investing in solar technology, with hopes of becoming a leader in the industry.
The future of solar power looks bright, with advancements in technology and increasing interest worldwide.
